e%20SAG-AFTRA%20strike%2C%20the%20largest%20ongoing%20action%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20there%20is%20no%20shortage%20of%20labor%20organizing%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20160%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-sag-aftra-actors-wga-writers-unions-strike-hollywood%5C%22%3ESAG-AFTRA%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20on%20strike%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%2C%20and%20another%2011%2C500%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-writers-strike-wga-picket-lines-streamers-studios-netflix-disney-2023-5%5C%22%3EWriters%20Guild%20of%20America%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20on%20strike%20for%20almost%20four%20months%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20another%2012%20other%20active%20strikes%20in%20the%20state%20during%20July%2C%20making%20California%20the%20most%20active%20state%20for%20labor%20actions%20that%20month%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Cornell%20University%20School%20of%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstriketracker.ilr.cornell.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELabor%20Action%20Tracker.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20tensions%20when%20a%20union%20decides%20to%20walk%20out%20is%20how%20long%20their%20striking%20members%20can%20survive%20without%20a%20paycheck.%20But%20that%20problem%20could%20be%20less%20of%20one%20if%20some%20California%20lawmakers%20get%20their%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegislators%20are%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flegiscan.com%2FCA%2Ftext%2FSB799%2Fid%2F2838492%2FCalifornia-2023-SB799-Amended.html%5C%22%3Econsidering%20a%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20make%20any%20striking%20workers%20in%20the%20state%20eligible%20for%20unemployment%20benefits%20if%20their%20action%20lasts%20more%20than%20two%20weeks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20passes%2C%20it%20would%20make%20California%20the%20third%20state%20in%20the%20nation%20to%20adopt%20such%20a%20policy%2C%20following%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F09%2Fwhere-workers-on-strike-can-qualify-for-unemployment-benefits.html%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20and%20New%20Jersey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F09%2Fwhere-workers-on-strike-can-qualify-for-unemployment-benefits.html%5C%22%3EConnecticut%20and%20Massachusetts%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20also%20considering%20similar%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELabor%20experts%20say%20the%20bill%20could%20mark%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20workers%20in%20California.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20will%20very%20much%20be%20a%20pro-labor%20statement%20at%20a%20time%20in%20a%20year%20when%20so%20many%20Californians%20have%20gone%20on%20strike%20and%20are%20hurting%2C%26quot%3B%20Steven%20Greenhouse%2C%20former%20New%20York%20Times%20labor%20reporter%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Century%20Foundation%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20certainly%20be%20a%20boon%20to%20them%20and%20in%20ways%20might%20help%20stimulate%20the%20California%20economy%20by%20putting%20more%20money%20in%20people's%20pockets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20bill%2C%20striking%20workers%20would%20be%20eligible%20for%20payments%20of%20up%20to%20%24450%20per%20week.%20New%20York%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdol.ny.gov%2Fyou-apply-unemployment-frequently-asked-questions%5C%22%3Eoffers%20striking%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20up%20to%20%24504%20a%20week%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnj.gov%2Flabor%2Fmyunemployment%2Fbefore%2Fabout%2Fcalculator%2F%5C%22%3ENew%20Jersey%3C%2Fa%3E%20offers%20up%20to%20%24830%20a%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20Jersey%20expanded%20its%20law%20in%20April%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.natlawreview.com%2Farticle%2Fnew-jersey-law-further-expands-striking-workers-eligibility-unemployment-benefits%5C%22%3Edecreasing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20waiting%20period%20for%20striking%20workers%20before%20benefits%20kick%20in%20from%2030%20to%2014%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStriking%20workers%20having%20access%20to%20unemployment%20benefits%20would%20also%20benefit%20the%20larger%20community%20in%20California%2C%20according%20to%20Kate%20Bronfenbrenner%2C%20director%20of%20labor%20education%20research%20at%20the%20Cornell%20University%20School%20of%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20remember%20the%20long-term%20costs%20of%20strikes%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20to%20workers%2C%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Bronfenbrenner%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20workers%20are%20on%20strike%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20money%20to%20make%20purchases%2C%20they're%20not%20shopping%2C%20they're%20late%20on%20their%20rents%20and%20their%20mortgage%20payments.%20So%20it's%20good%20for%20the%20community%20for%20workers%20to%20get%20unemployment%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Moutrie%2C%20a%20policy%20advocate%20for%20the%20California%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%2C%20however%2C%20called%20the%20proposal%20%26quot%3Birresponsible%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20would%20burden%20employers%20throughout%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia's%20UI%20system%20is%20already%20%2418%20billion%20in%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20Moutrie%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadvocacy.calchamber.com%2F2023%2F08%2F11%2Fcalchamber-issues-statement-on-proposal-to-provide-ui-payments-to-striking-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month.%20%26quot%3BAdding%20more%20costs%20to%20an%20insolvent%20system%20will%20extend%20the%20tax%20increases%20already%20underway%20from%20COVID-19.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Bronfenbrenner%20said%20she%20expects%20this%20bill%20to%20face%20less%20opposition%20in%20light%20of%20California's%20recent%20str