80%9D%20the%20rulers%20is%20ultra%20vires%20and%20illegal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E(The%20Union%20Government%20later%20abolished%20the%20privy%20purses%20and%20privileges%20of%20rulers%20of%20former%20Indian%20States%20through%20the%2026th%20Amendment%20Act%2C%201971.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20judgment%20in%20this%20case%2C%20then%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20M.%20Hidayatullah%20pointed%20out%20that%20if%20the%20Maharaja%20of%20Jhind%20were%20recognised%20as%20the%20Nizam%20of%20Hyderabad%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20application%20of%20Article%20366%20(22)%20%E2%80%93%20defining%20the%20Ruler%20of%20a%20former%20Indian%20state%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20action%20so%20wholly%20arbitrary%20as%20not%20to%20be%20protected%20by%20Article%20363%20(Bar%20to%20interference%20by%20courts%20in%20disputes%20arising%20out%20of%20certain%20treaties%2C%20agreements%2C%20etc.).%C2%A0%20Justice%20Hidayatullah%20observed%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20answer%20was%20that%20the%20President%20would%20never%20do%20so.%20But%20who%20would%20have%20thought%20in%201950%20that%20recognition%20of%20all%20the%20Rulers%20would%20be%20withdrawn%20by%20a%20single%20order%3F%20Therefore%2C%20extreme%20examples%20are%20necessary%20to%20solve%20extreme%20cases%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranaryanan%2C%20while%20concluding%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20arguments%20before%20the%20bench%2C%20referred%20to%20this%20observation%2C%20and%20questioned%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20Article%20367%20%E2%80%93%20dealing%20with%20Interpretation%20%E2%80%93%20to%20abolish%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20special%20status.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CUsing%20367%2C%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%98the%20legislature%20of%20not%20less%20than%20half%20of%20the%20states%E2%80%99%20could%20be%20read%20as%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20the%20law%20minister.%20You%20can%20say%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESankaranarayanan%20cited%20this%20extreme%20hypothetical%20example%20to%20question%20the%20Union%20Government%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emove%20to%20amend%20Article%20367%2C%20which%20provides%20guidelines%20to%20interpret%20the%20constitution.%20A%20new%20clause%20was%20added%20to%20Article%20367%2C%20replacing%20%E2%80%9CConstituent%20Assembly%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20referred%20to%20in%20Article%20370(3)%20by%20%E2%80%9CLegislative%20Assembly%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESankaranarayanan%20thus%20slammed%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20amending%20the%20constitution%20through%20the%20device%20of%20Article%20367%2C%20rather%20than%20Article%20368%2C%20and%20asked%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CIf%20they%20are%20allowed%20to%20do%20this%2C%20heavens%20know%20what%20they%20will%20do%20next.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Nitya%20Ramakrishnan%20set%20the%20tone%20of%20arguments%20by%20questioning%20the%20general%20assumption%20that%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20not%20integrated%20and%20that%20Central%20rule%20was%20aimed%20at%20it.%20She%20pointed%20out%20that%20political%20sovereignty%20rests%20with%20the%20people%20and%20there%20is%20a%20democratic%20pact%20which%20was%20a%20part%20of%20Article%20370.%20She%20suggested%20that%20if%20a%20change%20has%20to%20occur%2C%20then%20the%20recommendation%20has%20to%20emanate%20from%20an%20authority%20that%20is%20equal%20in%20mandate%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20referred%20to%20the%20interview%20that%20the%20former%20governor%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20Satyapal%20Malik%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsatya-pal-malik-full-interview-pulwama-modi%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dwith%2520corruption%2527).-%2CMalik%252C%2520who%2520was%2520governor%2520during%2520the%2520Pulwama%2520terrorist%2520attack%2520of%2Cthe%2520devastating%2520terrorist%2520attack%2520on%5C%22%3Egave%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20claimed%20that%20he%20did%20not%20even%20know%20on%20August%204%2C%202019%20that%20the%20Constitution%20(Application%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir)%20Order%20(CO)%20was%20being%20issued%20the%20following%20day%2C%20to%20withdraw%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20special%20status.%20The%20bench%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20this%20is%20a%20post-facto%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fb8wmHUhLvOI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESG%20says%20no%20intention%20of%20touching%20special%20provisions%20in%20Northeast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20bench%20recorded%20an%20important%20statement%20made%20by%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20no%20intention%20to%20touch%20the%20special%20provisions%20applicable%20to%20the%20north-eastern%20states.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20apprehension%20and%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20create%20apprehension%2C%20as%20it%20will%20have%20serious%20repercussions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20the%20bench.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20bench%20requested%20senior%20advocate%20Manish%20Tiwari%20not%20to%20discuss%20such%20apprehensions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Warisha%20Farasat%20relied%20on%20the%20legal%20doctrine%20of%20malice%20in%20law%20to%20challenge%20the%20events%20surrounding%20the%20dilution%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20as%20three%20former%20chief%20ministers%20of%20the%20state%20were%20in%20detention.%C2%A0%20She%20claimed%20that%20in%20these%20days%20of%20pre-legislative%20consultation%2C%20what%20the%20Union%20government%20did%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20dilution%20of%20Article%20370%20clearly%20smacked%20of%20malice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECJI%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20while%20responding%20to%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20suggested%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20never%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20permanent%20provision%20and%20that%20it%20was%20self-limiting%20after%20the%20state%20constitution%20came%20into%20force%20in%201957.%20Sankaranarayanan%20observed%20that%20this%20case%20is%20effectively%20about%20whether%20a%20power%20to%20dilute%20Article%20370%20exists%20and%20whether%20the%20procedure%20laid%20to%20exercise%20that%20power%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CJI%20asked%20succinctly%3A%20%E2%80%9CCan%20the%20constitution%20of%20a%20federating%20unit%20be%20superior%20to%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Union%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20respondents%20will%20begin%20their%20arguments%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692803430000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fimg.youtube.com%2Fvi%2Fb8wmHUhLvOI%2F0.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-day-9-extreme-examples-extreme-cases%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22During%20the%20ninth%20day%20of%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20expressed%20his%20view%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20never%20intended%20to%20be%20permanent%20and%20it%20was%20self-limiting%20after%20the%20state%20constitution%20came%20into%20force%20in%201957.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-day-9-extreme-examples-extreme-cases%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chandrayaan-3%3A%20List%20Of%20Countries%20That%20Made%20Successful%20Soft-Landing%20On%20Moon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20landed%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20on%20Wednesday%20(August%2023%2C%202023)%20at%206.04%20p.m.-%20the%20exact%20time%20when%20Vikram%20lander%20touched%20down%20at%20the%20Moon's%20South%20Pole.%20India%20has%20now%20become%20the%20first%20nation%20to%20land%20near%20the%20South%20Pole%2C%20which%20is%20a%20hot%20new%20destination%20since%20traces%20of%20water%20were%20found%20on%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20become%20the%20fourth%20country%20to%20achieve%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20moon.%20Before%20India%2C%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%20and%20China%20have%20achieved%20this%20remarkable%20feat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2012%2C%201959%2C%20Russia%2C%20then%20known%20as%20the%20USSR%2C%20became%20the%20first%20country%20to%20achieve%20a%20successful%20lunar%20landing.%20This%20was%20a%20hard-landed%20spacecraft%20but%20the%20country%20managed%20to%20soft-land%20seven%20years%20later%20in%201966.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201966%2C%20the%20US%20soft-landed%20on%20the%20moon%20a%20few%20months%20after%20Russia.%20The%20US%20already%20has%2011%20soft%20landings%20which%20is%20the%20most%20in%20the%20world.%20That's%20not%20all%2C%20US%20is%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20land%20twelve%20people%20on%20the%20moon%20through%20six%20space%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20China%20became%20the%20third%20country%20to%20land%20on%20the%20moon.%20On%20January%203%2C%202019%2C%20China%20became%20the%20first%20country%20to%20land%20a%20rover%20on%20the%20dark%20side%20of%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20explained%20why%20space%20agencies%20are%20racing%20to%20the%20moon's%20south%20pole.%20The%20agency%20said%20the%20presence%20of%20frozen%20water%20on%20the%20moon%20is%20one%20of%20the%20main%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20is%20a%20follow-on%20mission%20to%20Chandrayaan-2%20and%20its%20objectives%20are%20to%20demonstrate%20safe%20and%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%20roving%20on%20the%20Moon%2C%20and%20to%20conduct%20in-situ%20scientific%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rs%20600%20crore%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20was%20launched%20on%20July%2014%20on%20board%20the%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark-III%20(LVM-3)%20rocket%20and%20took%2041%20days%20to%20reach%20its%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692803340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F80t45upo_moon-from-vikram-lander-650_625x300_18_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-list-of-countries-that-made-successful-soft-landing-on-the-moon-4323441%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chandrayaan-3%3A%20India%20has%20become%20the%20fourth%20country%20to%20achieve%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20the%20moon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-list-of-countries-that-made-successful-soft-landing-on-the-moon-4323441%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-list-of-countries-that-made-successful-soft-landing-on-the-moon-4323441%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandrayaan-3-list-of-countries-that-made-successful-soft-landing-on-the-moon-4323441%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThis%20Is%20India's%20Time%26quot%3B%3A%20Gautam%20Adani%20On%20India's%20Chandrayaan-3%20Success%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOur%20nation's%20orbits%20continue%20to%20expand%2C%20said%20billio