%20anecdote%20regarding%20one%20such%20experience.%20%E2%80%9CA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20was%20coming%20to%20Delhi%20by%20train.%20I%20do%20not%20wear%20a%20burqa%2C%20niqab%20or%20hijab%2C%20which%20means%20one%20cannot%20identify%20my%20religion%20by%20looking%20at%20me.%20But%20what%20about%20one%E2%80%99s%20name%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20day%20a%20couple%2C%20with%20their%20six-%20or%20seven-year-old%20daughter%20was%20sitting%20opposite%20me.%20The%20girl%20was%20playing%20and%20talking%20with%20me.%20Soon%2C%20she%20asked%20my%20name%2C%20which%20I%20impulsively%20revealed%20and%20to%20which%20she%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%98Are%20you%20a%20Muslim%3F%E2%80%99%20When%20I%20said%20yes%2C%20she%20quickly%20retorted%2C%20%E2%80%98Why%20do%20you%20live%20here%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20you%20go%20to%20Pakistan%3F%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20left%20speechless.%20I%20did%20not%20know%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20her.%20After%20the%20exchange%2C%20neither%20her%20parents%20nor%20she%20spoke%20to%20me%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20journey.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fgo-to-pakistan-indian-muslims%5C%22%3EWhy%20I%20Will%20Never%20%E2%80%98Go%20to%20Pakistan%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFear%20not%20limited%20to%20any%20one%20class%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJournalist%20Rana%20Ayyub%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20elite%20class%2C%20but%20she%20recently%20shared%20her%20concerns%20about%20the%20religious%20identity%20of%20her%20family%20members%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%204%2C%20after%20the%20Jaipur%20Express%20killings%2C%20Rana%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20Instagram%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20loves%20his%20Friday%20prayers%20ritual.%20He%20applies%20%3Cem%3Eittar%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5Ba%20kind%20of%20perfume%5D%2C%20wears%20his%20crisp%20white%20kurta-pyjama%20and%20his%20Muslim%20skull%20cap%20before%20he%20walks%20to%20the%20neighbourhood%20mosque%20for%20the%20Juma%20namaz.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20has%20all%20the%20visual%20markers%20of%20a%20Muslim%20man.%20With%20the%20train%20incident%2C%20with%20the%20provocative%20speeches%2C%20the%20brazen%20killings%20and%20targeting%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20he%20%E2%80%93%20a%20privileged%20Muslim%20man%20%E2%80%93%20is%20safe%20enough%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAyyub%E2%80%99s%20post%20received%20around%20750%20comments%2C%20most%20of%20which%20relate%20similar%20fears%20and%20share%20ways%20adopted%20by%20people%20to%20avoid%20any%20untoward%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20user%20wrote%20that%20when%20any%20of%20her%20relatives%20is%20on%20the%20bus%20or%20train%2C%20she%20avoids%20using%20the%20Muslim%20greetings%20of%20%E2%80%98salaam%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ekhuda%20hafiz%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20phone.%20A%20student%20from%20West%20Bengal%20said%20that%20most%20of%20the%20students%20in%20his%20class%20are%20Hindus%20and%20that%20sometimes%20they%20raise%20slogans%20like%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Shri%20Ram%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20evokes%20fear%20in%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthor%20Rakshanda%20Jalil%20also%20belongs%20to%20the%20upper%20class%20like%20Rana%20Ayyub%20and%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20her%20privileges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Ffear-depression-in-indian-muslims-is-palpable-even-among-those-who-are-privileged%5C%22%3EFear%20and%20Depression%20in%20Indian%20Muslims%20Palpable%20Even%20Among%20Those%20who%20are%20%E2%80%98Privileged%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20she%20narrated%20how%20she%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20house%20in%20a%20posh%20area%20in%20South%20Delhi%2C%20in%20a%20building%20with%20Muslim%20home%20owners%20on%20every%20floor%20and%20an%20old%20mosque%20in%20proximity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20several%20visits%2C%20I%20eventually%20chickened%20out%20from%20buying%20that%20perfectly%20lovely%20apartment%20in%20a%20perfectly%20lovely%20neighbourhood%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23132722%2FGulbarg-society.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22301%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669346%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22167%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Muslim-dominated%20Gulbarg%20Society%20was%20burnt%20by%20mobs%20during%20the%202002%20Gujarat%20violence.%20Photo%3A%20Dawnpope%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20giant%2C%20invisible%20yet%20perfectly%20legible%20%E2%80%98X%E2%80%99%20marked%20on%20that%20building.%20The%20proximity%20to%20the%20mosque%2C%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20Muslim%20homeowners%20on%20every%20floor%20of%20that%20house%20in%20an%20otherwise%20entirely%20non-Muslim%20neighbourhood%2C%20brought%20visions%20of%20Ahmadabad%2C%20of%20the%20Gulbarg%20Society%2C%20of%20the%20brutal%20killing%20of%20Congress%20MP%20Ehsan%20Jafri%20and%20at%20least%2035%20others%20inside%20that%20ill-fated%20housing%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWell-meaning%2C%20liberal%20friends%20made%20me%20feel%20small%20and%20silly%20for%20my%20chicken%20heartedness.%20%E2%80%98Oh%20come%2C%20on!%E2%80%99%20they%20chided%2C%20%E2%80%98That%20was%20Gujarat!%20It%20can%E2%80%99t%20happen%20in%20Delhi.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20And%20worse%20still%2C%20there%20was%20the%20shaming%3A%20%E2%80%98You%20too%3F%20You%20with%20all%20your%20privileges%3F%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20think%20like%20this!%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20with%20all%20my%20privileges%20%E2%80%93%20of%20education%2C%20of%20class%2C%20of%20having%20friends%20in%20%E2%80%98high%20places%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20I%20feel%20scared%2C%20more%20scared%20than%20I%20have%20ever%20been%20in%20my%20entire%20life.%20I%20am%2060%20years%20old%20and%20confess%20to%20a%20crushing%20fear%2C%20one%20that%20weighs%20my%20chest%20with%20an%20inexorable%20weight%20and%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20breathe%20sometimes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarah%20hails%20from%20an%20upper%20middle-class%20family%20and%20shares%20a%20similar%20fear%20as%20that%20of%20Rana%20Ayyub.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%20I%20used%20to%20wait%20for%20Fridays%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20Friday%20arrives%2C%20I%20get%20anxious%20that%20some%20untoward%20incident%20might%20happen%20in%20a%20mosque.%20One%20day%20my%20father%20and%20brother%20were%20a%20little%20late%20in%20returning%20from%20Friday%20prayers%20and%20I%20got%20really%20worried.%20Papa%20never%20used%20to%20take%20his%20mobile%20phone%20while%20going%20to%20the%20mosque%20for%20Friday%20prayers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20I%20insist%20that%20he%20carries%20his%20phone.%20Even%20a%20slight%20delay%20in%20his%20return%20makes%20us%20call%20him%20anxiously%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Wherever%20I%20go%2C%20my%20religion%20reaches%20there%20first%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaukat*%20works%20in%20the%20Indian%20Railways%20and%20does%20not%20want%20to%20give%20any%20more%20information%20about%20his%20identity.%20He%20usually%20dons%20what%20is%20described%20as%20the%20stereotypical%20Muslim%20marker%20%E2%80%93%20kurta-pyjama%20and%20a%20beard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSee%2C%20there%20is%20a%20political%20atmosphere%20against%20Muslims%2C%20but%20people%20like%20us%20who%20can%20be%20easily%20identified%20get%20remarks%20like%2C%20%E2%80%98How%20did%20you%20end%20up%20in%20the%20railways%2C%20%3Cem%3Emian%3C%2Fem%3E%20ji%3F%E2%80%99%20Our%20abilities%20are%20sometimes%20questioned%20owing%20to%20our%20identity.%20There%20are%20in%20fact%20many%20tiny%20matters%20of%20everyday%20life%20in%20which%20the%20behaviour%20of%20people%20suggests%20that%20wherever%20I%20go%2C%20my%20religion%20reaches%20there%20first.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fnew-india-muslim-bigotry-cosmopolitan-privilege%5C%22%3EIn%20New%20India%2C%20a%20Muslim%20Rose%20Smells%20Different%20From%20a%20Hindu%20Rose%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20by%20chance%20there%20are%20two%20to%20four%20Muslim%20employees%20in%20a%20section%2C%20people%20begin%20remarking%20that%20the%20place%20has%20become%20like%20Pakistan.%20Sometimes%20they%20make%20such%20remarks%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20face%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98you%20are%20the%20ones%20ruling%20here.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20women%20from%20our%20families%20participate%20in%20office%20parties%20or%20functions%2C%20other%20women%20comment%20on%20their%20dress%20or%20headcovers%20and%20ask%20them%20why%20they%20need%20to%20dress%20up%20this%20way%20in%20the%20present%20age.%20It%20means%20something%20or%20the%20other%20is%20going%20on%20in%20their%20mind%20regarding%20our%20identity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prejudice%20and%20fear%20about%20Muslim%20identity%20are%20getting%20more%20and%20more%20deep-rooted%20each%20year.%20Osama%2C%20who%20works%20in%20an%20NGO%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20look%20like%20a%20Muslim%2C%20which%20is%20perhaps%20why%20when%20I%20am%20travelling%2C%20people%20start%20playing%20videos%20of%20inflammatory%20speeches%20in%20loud%20volume.%20I%20also%20feel%20that%20many%20times%2C%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20Muslim%20family%20in%20the%20train%20makes%20people%20from%20other%20communities%20uncomfortable%20and%20scared.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20I%20was%20traveling%20to%20Rajasthan%20at%20a%20time%20of%20communal%20tension%2C%20when%20I%20got%20a%20call%20from%20my%20brother.%20I%20offered%20him%20salaam%20as%20per%20my%20habit%20and%20he%20immediately%20told%20me%20not%20to%20do%20so.%20He%20also%20told%20me%20not%20to%20reveal%20my%20name%20to%20anyone%20after%20getting%20down%20at%20the%20station%20and%20give%20another%20name%20if%20needed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAreeb*%20is%20a%20corporate%20employee%20based%20in%20Kolkata.%20Regarding%20the%20prejudice%20against%20Muslims%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20people%20from%20other%20communities%20who%20are%20good%20to%20us%2C%20but%20now%20their%20opinion%20of%20Muslims%20in%20general%20seems%20to%20have%20changed%2C%20as%20appears%20from%20their%20conversations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20instance%2C%20a%20friend%20commented%20about%20a%20specific%20professional%20work%3A%20%E2%80%98So%20many%20Muslims%20have%20entered%20the%20profession%20and%20they%20are%20doing%20the%20work%20at%20random%20rates.%20They%20have%20ruined%20the%20market!%E2%80%99%20I%20wondered%20later%20if%20there%20was%20any%20need%20to%20add%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98Muslim%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20sentence%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20facing%20a%20mentality%20of%20hatred%20%E2%80%A6%20has%20become%20an%20existential%20curse%20for%20the%20Muslims.%20They%20have%20automatically%20set%20certain%20unspoken%20rules.%20For%20example%2C%20wherever%20they%20are%2C%20even%20while%20travelling%2C%20they%20find%20it%20better%20to%20stay%20unnoticed.%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20when%20you%20will%20become%20the%20target%20for%20the%20person%20in%20front%20of%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23134256%2FMuslim-woman-election.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22839%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23134256%2FMuslim-woman-election.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23134256%2FMuslim-woman-election-300x187.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669350%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22524%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharib*%2C%20a%20teacher%20at%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%2C%20also%20felt%20the%20change%20in%20the%20attitude%20of%20non-Muslims.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20often%20travelling%20as%20I%20did%20during%20my%20studies.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20used%20to%20travel%20in%20sleeper%20class%20and%20never%20realised%20that%20I%20was%20a%20Muslim%20who%20was%20being%20viewed%20in%20a%20different%20way.%20I%20used%20to%20travel%20like%20everyone%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20people%20offer%20namaz.%20Personally%2C%20I%20did%20not%20like%20it%20at%20the%20time.%20But%20others%20did%20not%20mind%20it.%20They%20instead%20gave%20space%20to%20offer%20the%20prayer.%20Out%20of%20respect%20they%20even%20stopped%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20until%20the%20prayer%20was%20over.%20But%20today%20if%20someone%20offers%20namaz%20even%20on%20their%20berth%2C%20people%20take%20offence.%20They%20start%20playing%20the%20Hanuman%20Chalisa%20on%20their%20mobile%20phones.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CEarlier%20we%20used%20to%20interact%20with%20anyone%20and%20everyone%20on%20the%20train%2C%20and%20that%20was%20the%20fun%20of%20it.%20But%20now%20I%20feel%20scared.%20We%20are%20scared%20of%20even%20uttering%20a%20word%20unless%20the%20fellow%20passenger%20starts%20the%20conversation%20himself.%20What%20caused%20this%20rift%3F%20Clearly%2C%20an%20opinion%20has%20been%20etched%20about%20us%20on%20a%20large%20scale.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20I%20strictly%20tell%20my%20Muslim%20friends%20and%20acquaintances%20not%20to%20carry%20food%20on%20the%20train%20and%20not%20to%20take%20part%20in%20any%20debate.%20In%20matters%20of%20dress%2C%20I%20have%20strictly%20instructed%20my%20sisters%20to%20not%20wear%20hijab%20and%20so%20on.%20I%20ask%20them%20to%20dress%20up%20like%20non-Muslims.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20because%20we%20are%20scared%2C%20but%20because%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20anything%20bad%20to%20happen%20to%20our%20loved%20ones.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20some%20extent%2C%20we%20are%20compromising%20with%20our%20identity%2C%20because%20there%E2%80%99s%20not%20much%20else%20we%20can%20do.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncreased%20challenges%20for%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20freedoms%20are%20discussed%20in%20Indian%20families%20only%20as%20long%20as%20they%20are%20conveniently%20affordable.%20The%20problems%20that%20women%20and%20girls%20generally%20face%20owing%20to%20their%20gender%20have%20compounded%20for%20Muslim%20women%2C%20with%20the%20additional%20burden%20of%20their%20religious%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecisions%20which%20were%20already%20difficult%2C%20such%20as%20those%20regarding%20traveling%20alone%2C%20education%20and%20employment%2C%20have%20the%20new%20aspect%20of%20religion%20added%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20a%20PUCL%20report%20states%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1032480%2Fkarnataka-hijab-ban-robbed-thousands-of-muslim-girls-of-access-to-education-says-pucl-report%5C%22%3E1%2C000%20female%20students%20had%20dropped%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20the%20hijab%20controversy%20in%20Karnataka%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20reports%20that%20Chetan%20Singh%20Chowdhary%2C%20who%20fired%20gunshots%20in%20the%20Jaipur-Mumbai%20Express%2C%20had%20asked%20a%20woman%20wearing%20a%20burqa%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fmumbai%2Fkillings-on-train-rpf-constable-forced-woman-in-burqa-to-say-jai-mata-di-at-gunpoint-finds-probe-8894264%2F%5C%22%3Echant%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Mata%20Di%E2%80%99%20at%20gunpoint%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20is%20religious%20identity%20or%20the%20hijab%20the%20only%20issue%3F%20Noman*%2C%20who%20studied%20at%20a%20prestigious%20university%20in%20Delhi%20and%20is%20currently%20employed%20as%20an%20assistant%20professor%20in%20a%20university%20in%20Bihar%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20attitude%20towards%20women%20after%20the%20recent%20incidents.%20Earlier%2C%20we%20used%20to%20worry%20about%20their%20safety%20because%20they%20were%20women.%20Now%2C%20being%20a%20Muslim%20has%20added%20to%20our%20worries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20young%20female%20relative%20of%20mine%20had%20to%20get%20admission%20into%20college%20and%20the%20family%20chose%20one%20that%20was%20nearby.%20Something%20similar%20happened%20with%20another%20relative.%20His%20daughter%20had%20made%20it%20to%20the%20merit%20list%20of%20a%20renowned%20college.%20But%20since%20it%20was%20seven%20to%20eight%20kilometres%20away%20from%20home%2C%20the%20elders%20in%20the%20house%20did%20not%20allow%20her%20to%20join%20it%2C%20and%20she%20had%20to%20enrol%20in%20a%20nearby%20college.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20wearing%20a%20niqab%2C%20burqa%20or%20hijab%20also%20face%20a%20similar%20fear.%20Imrana%20Khatoon%2C%20a%20housewife%20from%20Darbhanga%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20feel%20scared%20to%20step%20out%20of%20the%20house%20wearing%20a%20burqa%20now.%20God%20forbid%2C%20if%20there%20is%20any%20kind%20of%20tension%20in%20the%20current%20environment%2C%20we%20can%20be%20easily%20spotted.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20concern%20about%20fellow%20passengers%20in%20the%20train.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20it%20has%20become%20more%20important%20to%20hide%20one%E2%80%99s%20identity.%20In%20our%20religion%2C%20the%20thing%20%5Bveil%5D%20which%20was%20made%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20safety%20is%20becoming%20a%20cause%20of%20insecurity%20for%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwho-takes-exception-to-the-hijab%5C%22%3EWho%20Takes%20Exception%20to%20the%20Hijab%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehana*%20lives%20in%20Delhi%20and%20works%20in%20the%20media%20as%20a%20freelancer.%20She%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20wear%20a%20hijab%2C%20but%20I%20work%20from%20home%20most%20of%20the%20time%20according%20to%20my%20convenience.%20I%20have%20this%20option%2C%20but%20many%20women%20are%20in%20such%20jobs%20where%20they%20have%20to%20go%20out%20every%20day%2C%20and%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20environment%2C%20it%20is%20a%20big%20challenge%20for%20Muslim%20women.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehana%20is%20right.%20Not%20everyone%20has%20the%20freedom%20to%20opt%20for%20work%20from%20home.%20Nabila*%2C%20a%20primary%20school%20teacher%20from%20Madhubani%20in%20Bihar%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20has%20ever%20said%20anything%20to%20me%20openly%20till%20now.%20But%20sometimes%20in%20conversations%20or%20otherwise%2C%20there%20are%20certain%20words%20or%20certain%20behaviours%20which%20strike%20me%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20under%20pressure%20because%20of%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRecently%2C%20I%20had%20gone%20for%20departmental%20training%2C%20and%20as%20per%20habit%2C%20I%20was%20wearing%20a%20burqa.%20But%20before%20entering%20the%20training%20centre%2C%20I%20took%20it%20off.%20While%20doing%20so%20I%20felt%20as%20if%20I%20was%20being%20watched%20and%20that%20I%20should%20hurry%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPerhaps%20it%20is%20my%20own%20misconception%20or%20lack%20of%20self-confidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20knowingly%20or%20unknowingly%2C%20I%20have%20started%20trying%20to%20hide%20my%20identity%20while%20leaving%20the%20house.%20As%20far%20as%20fear%20is%20concerned%2C%20for%20me%20it%20is%20like%20experiencing%20an%20invisible%20world.%20My%20daughter%20is%20still%20young%2C%20but%20I%20want%20her%20not%20to%20adopt%20any%20religious%20identity.%20Whatever%20she%20wants%20to%20practice%20must%20remain%20within%20the%20house.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHijabs%20have%20also%20proved%20fatal%20for%20the%20professional%20lives%20of%20women.%20Delhi%20resident%20Shayla%20Irfan%20used%20to%20teach%20at%20a%20reputed%20school%2C%20but%20one%20day%20she%20was%20told%20that%20her%20students%20and%20their%20parents%20were%20not%20comfortable%20with%20her%20wearing%20a%20hijab%2C%20so%20she%20must%20give%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShayla%20left%20the%20job.%20Even%20in%20her%20next%20job%20interview%2C%20she%20was%20told%20that%20she%20would%20get%20the%20job%20if%20she%20removed%20her%20hijab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELubna%20Amir%2C%20a%20dentist%20from%20Pune%2C%20has%20a%20similar%20story.%20Despite%20being%20a%20topper%20in%20her%20studies%2C%20her%20Muslim%20identity%20came%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20getting%20a%20job.%20A%20renowned%20dental%20clinic%20asked%20her%20to%20remove%20her%20hijab%20in%20order%20to%20get%20a%20job%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELubna%20refused.%20She%20gave%20up%20her%20dream%20of%20doing%20clinical%20work%20and%20joined%20a%20bioinformatics%20company.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F8%2F3%2Fmuslim-women-in-india-allege-bias-in-hiring-for-jobs%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3Cem%3EAl-Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20us%20being%20Muslims%2C%20but%20a%20bigger%20problem%20is%20with%20our%20Muslim%20appearance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F13153956%2F2022_2img11_Feb_2022_PTI02_11_2022_000281B-1024x646.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F13153956%2F2022_2img11_Feb_2022_PTI02_11_2022_000281B-1024x646.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F13153956%2F2022_2img11_Feb_2022_PTI02_11_2022_000281B-300x189.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F13153956%2F2022_2img11_Feb_2022_PTI02_11_2022_000281B.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-581370%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMuslim%20women%20in%20hijab%20participate%20in%20a%20candle%20light%20march%20during%20a%20protest%20rally%20over%20the%20%E2%80%98hijab%E2%80%99%20ban%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20February%2011%2C%202022.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%20Photo%2FSwapan%20Mahapatra%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20media%20peddling%20fear%20at%20every%20doorstep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20article%2C%20Rakhshanda%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20suspect%20I%20am%20not%20alone%20in%20this.%20I%20feel%20this%20fear%20and%20depression%20among%20a%20great%20many%20Muslims%20in%20urban%20India.%20I%20hear%20it%20in%20their%20silences.%20I%20sense%20it%20in%20their%20steadfast%20refusal%20to%20get%20drawn%20into%20political%20debates.%20I%20notice%20it%20in%20their%20stoicism%20in%20the%20face%20of%20virulent%20hate%20swirling%20about%20in%20school%20and%20college%20WhatsApp%20groups.%20I%20spot%20it%20in%20the%20hastily%20withdrawn%20social%20media%20posts%20drawing%20attention%20to%20some%20recent%20communal%20outrage%20or%20atrocity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20bitter%20truth%20of%20Digital%20India%20is%20that%20WhatsApp%20groups%20are%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20delivering%20communal%20toxicity%20to%20every%20household.%20The%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20any%20apartment%20or%20society%20is%20a%20primary%20centre%20for%20supplying%20hatred%20round%20the%20clock%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20religious%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFake%20news%20and%20provocative%20messages%20against%20Muslims%20are%20continuously%20being%20shared%20in%20the%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20one%20such%20housing%20society%20in%20South%20Delhi.%20The%20group%20also%20includes%20two%20Muslim%20families%20who%20reside%20in%20the%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20some%20people%20and%20those%20Muslim%20members%20shared%20verified%20content%20and%20fact-check%20reports%20to%20counter%20the%20fake%20news%2C%20but%20communal%20messages%20kept%20pouring%20until%20they%20were%20tired%20of%20correcting%20and%20countering%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hatred%20against%20Muslims%20has%20increased%20to%20such%20an%20extent%20that%20during%20Ramzan%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2Frow-in-noida-society-over-namaz-muslims-allege-hanuman-chalisa-recited-to-stop-prayers%2Farticle66672966.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20Hanuman%20Chalisa%20was%20recited%20in%20a%20prominent%20society%20in%20Noida%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protest%20against%20namaz%20being%20offered%20at%20one%20place%20with%20the%20permission%20of%20the%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fup-bajrang-dal-disrupts-muslim-prayers-held-at-a-private-property-in-moradabad%5C%22%3EBajrang%20Dal%20members%20had%20created%20a%20ruckus%20in%20Moradabad%2C%20UP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20offering%20%3Cem%3Etarawih%3C%2Fem%3E%20prayers%20at%20a%20private%20property.%20The%20matter%20reached%20the%20police%2C%20who%20refused%20to%20grant%20permission%20to%20the%20property%20owner%20to%20organise%20the%20mass%20prayer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuslim%20families%20living%20in%20such%20hostile%20environments%20are%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20trust%20their%20neighbours%20or%20the%20people%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fa-cesspool-of-toxicity-occupies-a-central-place-in-our-democracy%5C%22%3ESocial%20Media%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20Cesspool%20of%20Toxicity%20%E2%80%93%20Now%20Occupies%20a%20Central%20Place%20in%20Our%20Democracy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFear%20among%20Muslims%20is%20not%20baseless%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20attempts%20have%20been%20made%20to%20dismiss%20the%20fears%20among%20the%20Muslim%20community%20and%20their%20growing%20suspicions.%20Hindutva%20leaders%20have%20often%20offered%20them%20advice%20%E2%80%98not%20to%20be%20afraid%E2%80%99.%20However%2C%20the%20Muslims%20do%20not%20agree%20with%20it%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShaukat%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CBrainwashing%20is%20now%20complete.%20Media%20is%20spewing%20poison%20all%20the%20time.%20In%20such%20an%20environment%2C%20one%20does%20not%20feel%20good%20deep%20inside.%20You%20may%20call%20it%20fear%20or%20whatever%2C%20%5Bbut%5D%20knowingly%20or%20unknowingly%2C%20there%20is%20a%20constant%20and%20lingering%20sense%20of%20worry.%20This%20is%20happening%20more%20blatantly%20against%20Muslims%20in%20New%20India%2C%20and%20this%20attitude%20has%20been%20ingrained%20into%20their%20personality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20call%20this%20fear%20and%20anxiety%20imaginary.%20One%20thing%20or%20another%20is%20happening%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarah%20comments%20on%20the%20impact%20this%20environment%20has%20on%20her%20mental%20health%20and%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20started%20having%20nightmares%20about%20being%20trapped%20in%20a%20communal%20riot%20and%20being%20completely%20helpless.%20When%20I%20shared%20this%20with%20my%20mother%20and%20some%20friends%2C%20they%20said%20they%20had%20similar%20experience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehana%20also%20enumerates%20some%20social%20aspects%20of%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20violence%20against%20Muslims.%20She%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20far%20as%20I%20have%20observed%20and%20understood%2C%20the%20Muslim%20people%20who%20are%20able%20to%20afford%20it%20are%20giving%20priority%20to%20traveling%20by%20personal%20vehicles%20or%20by%20air.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20do%20not%20want%20to%20invest%20in%20Hindu-dominated%20areas%2C%20fearing%20attacks.%20They%20are%20avoiding%20shopping%20in%20Hindu-dominated%20markets.%20Shopkeepers%20are%20not%20using%20Muslim%20names%20or%20boards%20with%20Urdu%20writing.%20Muslim%20people%20doing%20small%20jobs%20in%20homes%20or%20societies%20have%20reduced%20their%20visits%20to%20Hindu%20areas%20or%20societies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharib%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20mental%20condition%20is%20such%20that%20when%20we%20get%20together%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20for%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20having%20tea%20%E2%80%93%20we%20talk%20of%20nothing%20but%20similar%20news%20and%20share%20our%20worries%20about%20the%20situation%20in%20future.%20We%20have%20been%20reduced%20to%20nothing%20but%20our%20existence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERakshanda%20describes%20this%20fear%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%98look%E2%80%99%20like%20a%20Muslim%2C%20so%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20I%20am%20safe.%20Unless%20called%20out%20to%20chant%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Shri%20Ram%E2%80%99%20to%20profess%20my%20Indianness%2C%20I%20am%20largely%20safe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F9JoeadDatPc%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20what%20of%20my%20name%3F%20How%20can%20I%20camouflage%20that%20on%20a%20railway%20booking%20chart%3F%20Or%20hide%20it%20when%20asked%20to%20provide%20proof%20of%20identity%3F%20While%20my%20first%20name%20can%20afford%20some%20benefit%20of%20doubt%2C%20for%20it%20might%20pass%20as%20a%20Parsi%E2%80%99s%2C%20my%20surname%20is%20a%20dead%20give-away.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20push%20comes%20to%20shove%20in%20the%20New%20India%20that%20is%20Bharat%2C%20not%20even%20speaking%20English%20will%20give%20me%20an%20exit%20pass%20if%20a%20mob%20baying%20for%20Muslim%20blood%20were%20to%20%3Cem%3Egherao%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5Bsurround%5D%20me.%20All%20my%20so-called%20privileges%20can%20be%20brought%20to%20naught%20by%20a%20lumpen%20crowd.%20The%20realisation%20is%20chilling.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Areeb%2C%20these%20changes%20are%20not%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20today%20or%20tomorrow.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20happening%20as%20per%20a%20planned%20political%20strategy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSecondly%2C%20India%20is%20quickly%20becoming%20a%20society%20of%20people%20who%20do%20not%20step%20forward%20to%20rescue%20%5Bsomeone%5D%20if%20%5Bthey%20are%5D%20being%20targeted%20because%20of%20their%20religion%2C%20or%20if%20a%20situation%20like%20the%20Jaipur%20Express%20train%20arises.%20This%20is%20the%20mindset%20politics%20is%20toying%20with.%20Even%20if%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20no%20longer%20in%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20we%20are%20not%20going%20to%20easily%20get%20rid%20of%20this%20hatred%20and%20mentality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20dangerous%20for%20me%20to%20be%20identified%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20to%20comment%2C%20Faiyaz%20Ahmad%20Wajih%2C%20assistant%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20Urdu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20days%2C%20I%20am%20sensing%20a%20fearful%20silence%20a%20lot%20more%20around%20me.%20There%20is%20noise%20in%20this%20silence%2C%20but%20people%20are%20pretending%20as%20if%20everything%20is%20fine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20know%20people%20who%20are%20worried%20about%20their%20appearance%20and%20a%20dress%20that%20gives%20them%20away%20from%20a%20distance.%20This%20concern%20has%20escalated%20after%20the%20Jaipur%20Express%20murder%20case.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20some%20people%20may%20shave%20off%20their%20beard%20or%20stop%20wearing%20a%20niqab%2C%20but%20what%20about%20people%20who%20study%20in%20madrasas%20or%20work%20as%20imams%3F%20Can%20they%20take%20such%20a%20step%20out%20of%20fear%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20I%20do%20not%20call%20it%20fear%20among%20the%20Muslim%20community%2C%20my%20biggest%20concern%20is%3A%20can%20I%20one%20day%20be%20recognised%20as%20a%20Muslim%20too%3F%20That%20is%20going%20to%20be%20dangerous.%20Few%20people%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20this%20fear.%20Many%20Muslims%20have%20started%20keeping%20their%20religious%20identity%20hidden%20behind%20the%20cover%20of%20silence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMuslims%20feel%20that%20whenever%20they%20are%20or%20will%20be%20targeted%20for%20their%20religion%2C%20neither%20anyone%20from%20other%20communities%20nor%20even%20the%20police%20will%20come%20to%20their%20rescue.%20I%20could%20talk%20about%20hope%2C%20but%20the%20way%20the%20state%20has%20patronised%20hatred%20and%20the%20way%20slogans%20of%20genocide%20are%20raised%20in%20%3Cem%3Edharam%20sansads%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20there%20is%20not%20much%20hope%20visible.%20The%20Muslim%20community%20has%20been%20put%20to%20sacrifice%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20power.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAn%20asterisk%20indicates%20that%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20name%20has%20been%20changed.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20first%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F255744%2Ffears-of-indian-muslims-in-new-india%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%20Hindi%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20It%20was%20translated%20into%20English%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692790205000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F04201314%2FIMG_21