ubmarines%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692788347000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102984130%2Cimgsize-167598.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fpla-navys-sharks-get-stealthier-china-on-verge-of-producing-world-class-nuclear-submarines-report%2Farticleshow%2F102982747.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102982747.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20nuclear-powered%20submarines%2C%20nicknamed%20%E2%80%98Sharks%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20PLA%20navy%2C%20are%20becoming%20more%20stealthy%20and%20capable%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20report%20by%20the%20US%20Naval%20War%20College.%20The%20report%20claims%20that%20China%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20producing%20%E2%80%9Cworld-class%E2%80%9D%20nuclear%20submarines%20that%20can%20rival%20the%20Russian%20Akula-I%20class%20SSN%20in%20terms%20of%20propulsion%2C%20quieting%2C%20sensors%20and%20weapons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fpla-navys-sharks-get-stealthier-china-on-verge-of-producing-world-class-nuclear-submarines-report%2Farticleshow%2F102982747.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fpla-navys-sharks-get-stealthier-china-on-verge-of-producing-world-class-nuclear-submarines-report%2Famp_articleshow%2F102982747.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fpla-navys-sharks-get-stealthier-china-on-verge-of-producing-world-class-nuclear-submarines-report%2Famp_articleshow%2F102982747.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wife's%20Persistent%20Insistence%20On%20Living%20Separately%20Cruelty%20To%20Husband%3A%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20wife's%20%26quot%3Bpersistent%20insistence%26quot%3B%20on%20living%20separately%20from%20in-laws%20without%20a%20justifiable%20reason%20is%20%26quot%3Btorturous%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20husband%20and%20is%20an%20act%20of%20cruelty%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Suresh%20Kumar%20Kait%2C%20while%20granting%20divorce%20to%20an%20estranged%20couple%2C%20observed%20that%20unlike%20the%20West%2C%20in%20India%2C%20it%20is%20not%20usual%20for%20the%20son%20to%20get%20separated%20from%20his%20family%20and%20his%20wife%20becomes%20integral%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNormally%2C%20without%20any%20justifiable%20strong%20reason%2C%20she%20should%20never%20insist%20that%20her%20husband%20should%20get%20separated%20from%20the%20family%20and%20live%20with%20her%20separately%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20husband%2C%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20assailed%20a%20family%20court%20order%20refusing%20to%20grant%20divorce.%20He%20sought%20dissolution%20of%20marriage%20on%20several%20grounds%20under%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%20including%20that%20the%20wife%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bquarrelsome%20lady%26quot%3B%20who%20did%20not%20show%20respect%20to%20the%20elders%20at%20the%20matrimonial%20home%20and%20insisted%20that%20he%20reside%20separately%20from%20his%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNormally%2C%20no%20husband%20would%20tolerate%20and%20would%20like%20to%20be%20separated%20from%20his%20parents%20and%20other%20family%20members.%20The%20persistent%20efforts%20of%20respondent%20wife%20to%20constrain%20the%20appellant%20to%20be%20separated%20from%20the%20family%20would%20be%20torturous%20for%20the%20husband%20and%20would%20constitute%20an%20act%20of%20cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Neena%20Bansal%20Krishna%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20respondent%20(wife)%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20show%20any%20justifiable%20reason%20for%20her%20insistence%20to%20have%20separate%20residence...%20The%20only%20inference%20that%20can%20be%20drawn%20is%20that%20her%20insistence%20to%20live%20separately%20from%20the%20other%20family%20members%20was%20whimsical%20and%20had%20no%20justifiable%20reason.%20Such%20persistent%20insistence%20can%20only%20be%20termed%20as%20an%20act%20of%20cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20in%20a%20decision%20that%20it%20is%20not%20a%20common%20practice%20or%20desirable%20culture%20for%20a%20Hindu%20son%20in%20India%20to%20get%20separated%20from%20his%20parents%20at%20the%20instance%20of%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20son%20has%20a%20moral%20and%20legal%20obligation%20to%20take%20care%20of%20and%20maintain%20his%20parents%20when%20they%20become%20old%20and%2C%20if%20his%20wife%20makes%20an%20attempt%20to%20deviate%20from%20the%20custom%20prevalent%20in%20the%20society%2C%20she%20must%20have%20some%20justifiable%20reason%20for%20that%2C%20the%20court%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20India%2C%20generally%20people%20do%20not%20subscribe%20to%20the%20western%20thought%20where%2C%20upon%20getting%20married%20or%20attaining%20majority%2C%20the%20son%20gets%20separated%20from%20the%20family.%20In%20normal%20circumstances%2C%20the%20wife%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20family%20of%20the%20husband%20after%20her%20marriage%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20an%20acrimonious%20atmosphere%20at%20home%20cannot%20be%20a%20conducive%20environment%20for%20the%20parties%20to%20forge%20a%20cordial%20conjugal%20relationship%20and%2C%20the%20circumstances%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%20including%20the%20elusive%20conduct%20of%20the%20wife%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20is%20bound%20to%20be%20a%20source%20of%20mental%20cruelty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20parties%20have%20had%20