or-indian-muslims-from-interview-zubin-mehta%5C%22%3Ealleged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Times%20of%20India%3Cem%3E%20had%20removed%20just%20one%20line%20from%20an%20interview%20he%20recently%20gave%20to%20the%20newspaper%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20he%20said%20that%20he%20wishes%20Muslims%20in%20India%20are%20able%20to%20live%20in%20peace%20forever.%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98s%20report%20on%20this%20can%20be%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ftimes-of-india-removed-quote-on-wanting-peace-for-indian-muslims-from-interview-zubin-mehta%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20this%20interview%20is%20given%20below.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Good%20evening%2C%20ladies%20and%20gentlemen.%20Before%20I%20begin%20my%20conversation%20with%20Mr%20Mehta%2C%20let%20me%20say%20that%20magical%20music%20performance%20is%20living%20proof%20that%20the%20spirit%20of%20India%20survived%202014.%20And%20this%20young%20generation%2C%20this%20young%20generation%20will%20keep%20the%20spirit%20of%20India%20alive%20no%20matter%20who%20rules%20us%20or%20for%20how%20long%20they%20rule%20us.%20And%20can%20I%20add%2C%20sir%2C%20your%20father%20would%20have%20been%20looking%20down%20from%20heaven%20smiling%20and%20he%20would%20have%20said%20to%20himself%20these%20children%20have%20given%20my%20Foundation%20life%2C%20meaning%2C%20and%20specific%20beauty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20thank%20you.%20That%20was%20the%20most%20magnificent%20thing%20I%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%20Ladies%20and%20gentlemen%2C%20before%20I%20actually%20start%20talking%20to%20Mr%20Mehta%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20tell%20you%20a%20story%20about%20the%20very%20first%20time%20I%20met%20him.%20He%20won%E2%80%99t%20remember%2C%20I%20can%20promise%20you.%20It%20was%2030%20years%20ago%2C%201994-95%2C%20you%E2%80%99d%20come%2C%20sir%2C%20with%20the%20Israeli%20Philharmonic%20Orchestra%2C%20and%20in%20those%20days%20there%20was%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20private%20television%20in%20India.%20There%20was%20no%20independent%20television.%20We%20would%20make%20programs%20on%20videos%2C%20and%20the%20one%20I%20worked%20on%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98Eyewitness%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDoordarshan%20got%20in%20touch%20and%20said%20could%20we%20collaborate%20to%20do%20an%20interview%20with%20Mr%20Mehta%2C%C2%A0%20and%20I%20said%20of%20course%20it%20would%20be%20a%20pleasure.%20And%20since%20it%20was%20Doordarshan%E2%80%99s%20idea%2C%20the%20interview%20was%20arranged%20and%20fixed%20by%20them.%20And%20they%20chose%20nine%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20I%20said%20to%20myself%20that%E2%80%99s%20an%20ungodly%20hour%20of%20the%20day!%20But%20since%20Mr%20Mehta%20has%20agreed%2C%20nine%20in%20the%20morning%20it%20is.%20And%20then%20I%20discovered%20that%20the%20night%20before%20was%20your%20grand%20performance%20in%20Delhi.%20So%20I%20said%20he%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20have%20a%20very%20short%20night%20of%20sleep%20before%20he%20comes%20to%20me.%20So%20we%20arrived%2C%20we%20set%20up%2C%20the%20crew%20and%20I%20were%20ready%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20was%20the%20Meridian%20Hotel%20where%20you%20were%20staying.%20And%20they%E2%80%99d%20given%20us%20a%20room%20for%20the%20recording%20at%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20corridor%20from%20your%20suite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20at%208.30%20we%20were%20ready%2C%20and%20we%20waited.%209%20o%E2%80%99clock%20came%20but%20Mr%20Mehta%20didn%E2%80%99t.%209.15%20came%20but%20Mr%20Mehta%20hadn%E2%80%99t.%209.20%2C%209.25%2C%209.30%2C%20and%20at%209.30%20I%20said%20to%20myself%20I%20wonder%20if%20something%E2%80%99s%20gone%20wrong.%20So%20I%20walked%20down%20the%20corridor%2C%20gently%20knocked%20on%20the%20door.%20No%20reply.%20I%20knocked%20a%20little%20harder.%20No%20reply.%20I%20tried%20the%20bell%20tentatively%2C%20it%20rang%20once%2C%20nothing%2C%20I%20tried%20it%20again%2C%20nothing.%20By%20that%20stage%2C%20I%20was%20ringing%20the%20bell%2C%20knocking%20on%20the%20door%2C%20calling%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Mehta%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20then%20suddenly%20the%20door%20opened%20and%20there%20he%20was%20%E2%80%93%20in%20your%20magnificent%20pyjamas%20and%20dressing%20gown%2C%20rubbing%20your%20eyes%20and%20you%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CChrist!%20I%20am%20going%20to%20be%20interviewed%20by%20the%20only%20man%20in%20this%20country%20who%20comes%20on%20time!%E2%80%9D%20I%20will%20never%20forget%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Where%20was%20it%2C%20in%20Bombay%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20No%2C%20it%20was%20at%20the%20Meridian%20Hotel%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Delhi!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20think%20it%20was%20on%20the%2030th%20floor%2C%20if%20I%20remember.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F_DH2sraXhZ4%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Yeh%20Hai%20Bombay%2C%20Meri%20Jaan%3A%20Zubin%20Mehta%20in%20conversation%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Mr%20Mehta%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20start%20at%20the%20very%20beginning.%20In%20your%20autobiography%2C%20you%20write%20I%20was%20a%20perfectly%20normal%20young%20boy%2C%20cheeky%20and%20in%20no%20way%20averse%20to%20the%20usual%20pranks%20and%20fights.%20You%20also%20say%20you%20had%20a%20loving%2C%20tenderly%20caring%20mother%20and%20a%20wonderful%20father.%20So%20was%20the%20young%20Zubin%20naughty%2C%20and%20was%20he%20pampered%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20so.%20My%20brother%20was%20naughty%2C%20the%20young%20one.%20He%20gave%20my%20mother%20a%20bad%20time%20when%20he%20was%20very%20young.%20Later%20on%20he%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20tell%20me%2C%20did%20I%20put%20on%20some%20decent%20clothes%20after%20that%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20You%20did!%20I%20mean%20you%20said%20give%20me%2020%20minutes%2C%20and%20you%E2%80%99d%20had%20a%20shave%2C%20you%E2%80%99d%20had%20a%20bath%20and%20you%20came%20smelling%20of%20the%20most%20magnificent%20aftershave%20because%20I%20remember%20the%20cameraman%20said%20to%20you%20sir%20you%20smell%20good.%20%5BLaughter%5D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Really!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20So%20you%20were%20the%20goody%20goody%20in%20the%20family%3F%20You%20were%20mummy%E2%80%99s%20pet%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that.%20You%20ask%20my%20brother%20that.%20He%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20agree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20You%20describe%20your%20family%20as%20an%20old-fashioned%20Parsi%20family.%20At%20another%20point%20in%20your%20autobiography%2C%20you%20call%20it%20a%20traditional%20Parsi%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20absolutely%20true.%20That%20had%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20with%20my%20grandparents%20too.%20Every%20night%20after%20dinner%2C%20my%20grandfather%20had%20my%20brother%20and%20myself%2C%20and%20he%20taught%20us%20our%20prayers%20and%20he%20taught%20us%20arithmetic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20And%20are%20you%20good%20at%20it%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Yeah%2C%20in%20those%20days%20I%20could%20say%20my%2017%20times%20tables%2C%20my%2019%20times%20tables%2C%20and%20he%20was%20that%20typical%20Parsi%20educated%2C%20counting%20on%20his%20fingers%2C%20and%20I%20still%20only%20counted%20Gujarati.%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20it%20any%20other%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%20is%20terrific.%20What%20is%2024%20in%20Gujarati%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20That%20came%20from%20my%20grandfather.%20My%20father%20taught%20me%20music%20and%20taught%20me%20to%20appreciate%20music%2C%20because%20he%20sat%20with%20me%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20also%2C%20and%20we%20would%20play%20records.%20He%20had%20a%20wonderful%20collection%2C%20so%20when%20I%20went%20to%20Vienna%2C%20I%20knew%20a%20lot%20of%20music%20that%20I%20had%20heard%20at%20home.%20I%20knew%20more%20than%20most%20of%20the%20students%20in%20my%20class%20because%20I%20had%20heard%20these%20recordings%20of%20Toscanini%20and%20Furtwangler%20and%20Stokowski.%20The%20records%20in%20those%20days%20were%20terrible%20sounding%2C%20but%20their%20Tempe%2C%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20music%2C%20that%20was%20correct.%20I%20heard%20from%20my%20youth%2C%20and%20the%20first%20time%20I%20heard%20an%20orchestra%20in%20Vienna%20I%20thought%20my%20ears%20popped%20open%2C%20I%20had%20never%20heard%20anything%20like%20that.%20So%20there%20was%20quite%20an%20evolution%20in%20my%20hearing%20and%20I%20that%20became%20my%20emblem%2C%20my%20axiom%2C%20all%20my%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20want%20very%20much%20to%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20your%20father%E2%80%99s%20influence%20on%20your%20music%2C%20and%20also%20his%20gramophone.%20But%20first%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20school.%20Your%20parents%20sent%20you%20to%20Saint%20Mary%E2%80%99s%20High%20School.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EZM%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20No%2C%20first%20to%20Campion%2