ink%2C%20can%20unlock%20the%20door%20to%20instant%20nirvana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExaggerated%20though%20this%20view%20might%20be%2C%20there%20is%20no%20denying%20that%20trade%20and%20investments%20have%20enhanced%20our%20well-being.%20No%20wonder%20few%20institutions%20can%20rival%20the%20vice-like%20grip%20of%20the%20marketplace%20on%20our%20collective%20imagination.%20Yet%2C%20in%20recent%20times%2C%20flagrant%20corporate%20skullduggery%2C%20fraud%20and%20manipulation%20have%20left%20us%20distrustful.%20We%20are%20appalled%20by%20the%20environmental%20destruction%20wrought%20by%20businesses%20and%20their%20exploitative%20labor%20practices.%20The%20Enron%20scandal%2C%20the%20Exxon%20Valdez%20and%20BP%20oil%20spills%2C%20the%20Volkswagen%20deception%2C%20and%20the%20offshore%20shell%20companies%20and%20dubious%20transactions%20of%20businesses%2C%20as%20revealed%20in%20the%20Panama%2C%20Paradise%20and%20Pandora%20papers%2C%20have%20eroded%20our%20faith%20in%20capitalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aberrations%20of%20the%20business%20world%2C%20the%20social%20pathologies%20they%20engender%2C%20spring%20from%20a%20mistaken%20view%20that%20the%20only%20legitimate%20objective%20of%20a%20business%20is%20to%20be%20profitable%20and%20augment%20shareholder%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20self-serving%20doctrine%20has%20become%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20capitalist%20ethos.%20Business%20schools%20assiduously%20perpetuate%20this%20mythology.%20The%20faceless%20investor%20is%20now%20the%20unchallenged%20monarch%20who%20has%20to%20be%20humoured%20at%20all%20costs.%20To%20gloss%20over%20the%20single-minded%20pursuit%20of%20profits%20above%20all%20else%2C%20businesses%20espouse%20corporate%20social%20responsibility%2C%20a%20vacuous%20agenda%20betokening%20the%20triumph%20of%20symbol%20over%20substance.%20Such%20welfare%20programmes%20barely%20camouflage%20the%20predatory%20practices%20of%20the%20business%20world.%20Discerning%20observers%20are%20dismayed%20to%20the%20point%20of%20declaring%20that%20profits%20and%20purpose%20are%20incompatible.%20Businesses%2C%20they%20aver%2C%20are%20inherently%20incapable%20of%20being%20virtuous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20329px)%2085vw%2C%20329px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115348%2F41rbURSZCRL.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22329%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115348%2F41rbURSZCRL.jpeg%20329w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115348%2F41rbURSZCRL-197x300.jpeg%20197w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669315%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGeoffrey%20Jones%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDeeply%20Responsible%20Business%3A%20A%20Global%20History%20of%20Values-Driven%20Leadership%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHarvard%20University%20Press%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Geoffrey%20Jones%2C%20Isidor%20Straus%20Professor%20of%20Business%20History%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20and%20a%20Fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20International%20Business%2C%20rejects%20this%20view.%20He%20argues%20that%20with%20visionary%20and%20value-driven%20leaders%2C%20businesses%20can%20be%20simultaneously%20purpose-driven%20and%20profitable.%20In%20his%20new%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EDeeply%20Responsible%20Business%3A%20A%20Global%20History%20of%20Values-Driven%20Leadership%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Harvard%20University%20Press%20this%20year%2C%20Prof.%20Jones%20subverts%20received%20wisdom%20about%20the%20logic%20of%20business%20and%20capitalism.%20He%20makes%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20reimagining%20capitalism%20and%20posits%20that%20the%20first%20step%20in%20this%20process%20is%20to%20reconceptualise%20business%20and%20its%20social%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Jones%2C%20the%20fundamental%20responsibility%20of%20business%20is%20to%20advance%20human%20flourishing%2C%20not%20just%20the%20prosperity%20of%20shareholders.%20He%20says%20businesses%20must%20be%20wedded%20to%20what%20he%20calls%20%E2%80%98deep%20responsibility%E2%80%99%20predicated%20on%20honesty%2C%20fairness%2C%20loyalty%2C%20compassion%2C%20courage%20and%20generosity.%20A%20deeply%20responsible%20business%2C%20Jones%20avers%20is%20committed%20to%20fully%20realising%20human%20potential.%20It%20is%20imbued%20with%20spirituality%20in%20that%20it%20never%20loses%20sight%20of%20the%20interconnectedness%20of%20all%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJones%20identifies%20three%20characteristics%20of%20deeply%20responsible%20business%20leaders.%20First%2C%20they%20choose%20an%20industry%20with%20some%20form%20of%20social%20value%20that%20is%20not%20actively%20harmful.%20Second%2C%20deeply%20responsible%20leaders%20do%20not%20engage%20in%20harmful%20or%20exploitative%20relationships%20with%20stakeholders%20such%20as%20investors%2C%20employees%2C%20suppliers%2C%20customers%20and%20the%20government.%20They%20interact%20with%20purpose%20and%20humility.%20Third%2C%20deeply%20responsible%20leaders%20support%20communities%20and%20contribute%20to%20their%20vitality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELest%20you%20dismiss%20his%20ideas%20as%20eccentric%20or%20utopian%2C%20Jones%20provides%20examples%20of%20deeply%20responsible%20business%20leaders%20worldwide%20who%20successfully%20blended%20profits%20with%20purpose%20and%20made%20stellar%20contributions%20to%20their%20communities.%20George%20Cadbury%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Cadbury%E2%80%99s%20chocolate%20company%20in%20Britain%2C%20inspired%20by%20Quaker%20values%2C%20worked%20ceaselessly%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20his%20workers.%20He%20opposed%20sweatshops%2C%20campaigned%20for%20old-age%20pensions%2C%20and%20supported%20labor%20unions.%20Cadbury%20disliked%20inequality.%20He%20treated%20his%20workers%20with%20dignity%2C%20established%20welfare%20policies%2C%20and%20provided%20affordable%20housing%20to%20the%20poor%20in%20Bournville%2C%20a%20new%20township%20in%20Birmingham%2C%20UK.%20A%20man%20ahead%20of%20his%20time%2C%20Cadbury%20opposed%20British%20imperialism%20and%20armed%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEdward%20Filene%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Filene%E2%80%99s%20department%20stores%20chain%20in%20Boston%2C%20which%20much%20later%20became%20Macy%E2%80%99s%2C%20was%20an%20American%20entrepreneur%20and%20philanthropist%20deeply%20devoted%20to%20the%20well-being%20of%20his%20employees.%20A%20proponent%20of%20%E2%80%98industrial%20democracy%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20equal%20distribution%20of%20wealth%2C%20he%20paid%20his%20workers%20sumptuously%20and%20gave%20them%20an%20active%20role%20in%20running%20his%20business.%20Filene%20also%20established%20credit%20unions%20to%20help%20the%20less%20privileged%20and%20was%20hailed%20as%20the%20father%20of%20the%20credit%20union%20movement%20in%20America.%20He%20was%20deeply%20invested%20in%20his%20city%2C%20Boston%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20make%20it%20a%20world-class%20metropolis.%20Filene%20also%20worked%20with%20the%20Catholic%20archbishop%20of%20Boston%20to%20set%20up%20the%20Boston%20Dwelling%20House%20Company%2C%20a%20venture%20for%20providing%20low-income%20housing%20for%20the%20underprivileged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Germany%2C%20Robert%20Bosch%2C%20industrialist%2C%20engineer%2C%20and%20founder%20of%20Robert%20Bosch%20GmbH%2C%20pioneered%20pro-labor%20policies.%20He%20paid%20high%20salaries%20to%20his%20employees%20and%20invested%20heavily%20in%20their%20training.%20In%20addition%2C%20he%20provided%20housing%20and%20libraries%20for%20his%20workers%20and%20supported%20collective%20bargaining.%20A%20proponent%20of%20socialism%2C%20Bosch%20was%20keen%20on%20promoting%20the%20autonomy%20and%20well-being%20of%20his%20workers.%20His%20company%20was%20the%20first%20to%20introduce%20eight-hour%20workdays.%20Bosch%20donated%20generously%20to%20humanitarian%20and%20educational%20causes.%20A%20great%20believer%20in%20homeopathy%2C%20he%20donated%205.5%20million%20marks%20on%20his%2075th%20birthday%20for%20starting%20a%20full-scale%20homeopathic%20Robert%20Bosch%20Hospital.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20most%20business%20leaders%2C%20motivated%20by%20their%20self-interest%2C%20did%20not%20speak%20out%20against%20the%20Nazis%2C%20Bosch%20actively%20criticised%20their%20policies%20and%20opposed%20them.%20Guided%20by%20his%20convictions%2C%20he%20helped%20Jews%20persecuted%20by%20Hitler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJones%20applauds%20several%20Indian%20businessmen%20for%20their%20singular%20display%20of%20deep%20responsibility.%20He%20lauds%20the%20pioneering%20work%20of%20Indian%20business%20barons%20like%20Ghanshyam%20Das%20Birla%2C%20Jamnalal%20Bajaj%2C%20and%20Lalbhai%20Kasturbhai.%20Lalbhai%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20developing%20the%20Bombay%20Plan%20in%201944%2C%20which%20delineated%20the%20role%20of%20the%20government%20in%20forging%20economic%20policy.%20As%20an%20industrialist%2C%20he%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20new%20chemical%20and%20textile%20sectors.%20A%20close%20associate%20of%20Gandhi%2C%20he%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20Tilak%20Swaraj%20Fund%2C%20set%20up%20by%20Gandhi%20in%201921%20to%20collect%20one%20crore%20rupees%20to%20fund%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%20struggle.%20Besides%2C%20he%20set%20up%20the%20Gujarat%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20and%20tirelessly%20worked%20to%20promote%20education%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Ahmedabad%20Education%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJones%20also%20praises%20the%20Parsis%20as%20exemplars%20of%20deep%20responsibility.%20A%20prominent%20figure%20among%20them%20was%20Jamsetji%20Jeejeebhoy%2C%20a%20Parsi%20merchant%20in%20Mumbai%20who%20grew%20rich%20trading%20cotton%20and%20opium%20to%20China%20during%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%2019th%20century.%20He%20experienced%20penury%20in%20his%20younger%20days%20and%20wanted%20to%20help%20distressed%20people.%20Jeejeebhoy%20set%20up%20several%20hospitals%20and%20schools%20and%20donated%20to%20several%20worthy%20causes.%20A%20fellow%20Parsi%2C%20Jamshetji%20Nusserwanji%20Tata%2C%20widely%20regarded%20as%20the%20Father%20of%20Indian%20Industry%2C%20was%20also%20a%20redoubtable%20philanthropist.%20A%20textile%20tycoon%20who%20later%20branched%20into%20iron%20and%20steel%2C%20hydroelectric%20power%2C%20hotels%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%20Tata%20had%20the%20Midas%20touch%20in%20business.%20Success%20did%20not%20make%20him%20oblivious%20to%20social%20obligations.%20Tata%20was%20famously%20large-hearted%20in%20his%20altruism.%20As%20Jones%20points%20out%2C%20he%20was%20greatly%20inspired%20by%20the%20Zoroastrian%20teaching%20that%20%E2%80%98poverty%20and%20suffering%20are%20an%20affliction%20of%20evil%2C%E2%80%99%20and%20removing%20them%20requires%20%E2%80%98constructive%E2%80%99%20not%20%E2%80%98patchwork%E2%80%99%20philanthropy.%20Galvanised%20by%20this%20vision%2C%20Tata%20set%20up%20several%20hospitals%2C%20schools%2C%20and%20institutions%20of%20higher%20learning%2C%20most%20notably%2C%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science.%20He%20also%20set%20up%20the%20J.N.%20Tata%20Endowment%20for%20the%20Higher%20Education%20of%20Indians%20in%201892%2C%20which%20helped%20thousands%20of%20deserving%20students%20pursue%20their%20educational%20dreams.%20One%20of%20his%20enduring%20legacies%20was%20transforming%20a%20sleepy%2C%20nondescript%20village%2C%20Sakchi%2C%20into%20Jamshedpur%2C%20a%20modern%20city%20he%20built%20in%20Jharkhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jamshetji%20Tata%20of%20Japan%20was%20a%20serial%20entrepreneur%2C%20visionary%2C%20and%20doyen%20of%20business%2C%20Shibusawa%20Eiichi.%20He%20launched%20500%20companies%20during%20his%20lifetime.%20Hailed%20as%20the%20Father%20of%20Japanese%20capitalism%2C%20Shibusawa%20earned%20his%20spurs%20for%20setting%20up%20the%20Dai%E2%80%99ichi%20Bank%20%E2%80%93%20First%20National%20Bank%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20modern%20bank%20of%20Japan%20based%20on%20joint%20stock%20ownership.%20He%20accorded%20great%20importance%20to%20investing%20in%20people%20and%20was%20dedicated%20to%20making%20them%20prosperous%20through%20economic%20activity.%20Shibusawa%20favored%20%3Cem%3EGapponshugi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20capitalism%20infused%20with%20moral%20values.%20He%20encouraged%20women%E2%80%99s%20education%20and%20patronised%20several%20educational%20and%20entrepreneurial%20ventures.%20Like%20Tata%2C%20Shibusawa%20is%20well-known%20for%20founding%20the%20Denenchofu%20Garden%20City%2C%20a%20self-sustainable%20garden%20city%20supervised%20by%20a%20socially%20oriented%20corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20440px)%2085vw%2C%20440px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115519%2Fheadshot.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115519%2Fheadshot.jpeg%20440w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115519%2Fheadshot-284x300.jpeg%20284w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-669316%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22464%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGeoffrey%20Jones.%20Photo%3A%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJones%E2%80%99%20history%20of%20deeply%20responsible%20business%20leaders%20underscores%20two%20crucial%20points.%20First%2C%20though%20hugely%20successful%2C%20primarily%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20diligence%2C%20a%20robust%20business%20sense%2C%20and%20luck%2C%20they%20did%20not%20lose%20sight%20of%20their%20social%20obligations.%20What%20was%20common%20to%20Cadbury%2C%20Filene%2C%20Bosch%2C%20Tata%2C%20Shibusawa%2C%20and%20others%20was%20that%20they%20combined%20their%20staggering%20business%20acumen%20with%20an%20abiding%20devotion%20to%20enhancing%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%20in%20their%20communities.%20Unlike%20business%20magnates%20of%20our%20times%2C%20they%20did%20not%20park%20their%20profits%20in%20tax%20havens.%20Instead%2C%20they%20answered%20a%20higher%20calling%20and%20bowed%20to%20the%20imperatives%20of%20social%20solidarity.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20did%20not%20neglect%20their%20bottom%20line.%20These%20deeply%20responsible%20leaders%20instantiate%20that%20advancing%20human%20capabilities%20and%20earning%20popular%20goodwill%20are%20high-return%20investments%20in%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20though%20exceptional%2C%20the%20accomplishments%20of%20deeply%20responsible%20businessmen%20were%20not%20unblemished.%20They%2C%20too%2C%20were%20fashioned%20from%20the%20crooked%20timber%20of%20humanity.%20A%20singular%20strength%20of%20Jones%E2%80%99%20book%20is%20its%20measured%20appraisal%20of%20deeply%20responsible%20leaders.%20He%20astutely%20notes%20their%20imperfections%20and%20explains%20why%20they%20matter.%20George%20Cadbury%20was%20controlling.%20Filene%20was%20abrasive%20and%20annoying.%20Bosch%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Nazis%3B%20Hitler%20gave%20him%20a%20state%20funeral.%20Shibusawa%20Eiichi%20supported%20Japanese%20imperialist%20policies%20and%20urged%20women%20to%20be%20good%20mothers%20and%20wives.%20Though%20initially%20well-intentioned%2C%20Anita%20Roddick%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20iconic%20Body%20Shop%2C%20lied%20and%20ill-treated%20her%20workers.%20Albeit%20flawed%2C%20these%20business%20leaders%20were%20animated%20by%20a%20humanistic%20vision%2C%20and%20their%20work%20was%20leavened%20by%20their%20deep%20philosophical%20convictions%20and%20religious%20values%20in%20some%20cases.%20Moreover%2C%20they%20proved%20that%2C%20despite%20frailties%2C%20one%20can%20actualise%20ideals%20and%20give%20a%20good%20account%20of%20oneself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20one%20might%20quibble%20about%20the%20longevity%20of%20the%20edifying%20business%20practices%20discussed%20in%20the%20book.%20In%20several%20instances%2C%20the%20original%20idealism%20of%20the%20business%20moguls%20died%20after%20their%20demise.%20Cadbury%E2%80%99s%2C%20for%20example%2C%20changed%20hands%20several%20times.%20Mondelez%20International%2C%20the%20second-largest%20confectionery%20brand%20in%20the%20world%2C%20now%20owns%20it.%20In%20its%20latest%20incarnation%20as%20Macy%E2%80%99s%2C%20Filene%E2%80%99s%20department%20store%20is%20now%20owned%20by%20Federated%20Department%20Stores.%20In%20both%20instances%2C%20they%20have%20become%20regular%2C%20unremarkable%20businesses.%20They%20have%20little%20interest%20in%20furthering%20the%20ennobling%20legacies%20of%20their%20founders.%20Several%20deeply%20responsible%20businesses%20of%20the%20past%20have%20now%20become%20unrecognisable%20compared%20to%20earlier%2C%20meritorious%20manifestations.%20This%20distressing%20metamorphosis%20raises%20troubling%20questions%20about%20the%20sustainability%20of%20deep%20responsibility%20as%20a%20business%20model.%20A%20true%20believer%2C%20Jones%20avows%20the%20potency%20of%20deep%20responsibility.%20Why%2C%20then%2C%20is%20it%20not%20being%20taught%20in%20business%20schools%3F%20Jones%20candidly%20acknowledges%20that%20his%20institution%20%E2%80%93%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20%E2%80%93%20tried%20and%20failed%20long%20ago.%20It%20is%20now%20reputed%20for%20purveying%20shareholder%20capitalism.%20He%20chronicles%20attempts%20by%20Wallace%20Donham%2C%20the%20second%20Dean%20of%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School%2C%20to%20introduce%20ethics%20and%20social%20responsibility%20in%20the%20business%20curriculum%20in%20the%20Depression%20era.%20Donham%20wanted%20to%20teach%20business%20students%20philosophy%2C%20history%2C%20and%20the%20social%20sciences%20to%20stimulate%20creative%20and%20critical%20thinking.%20He%20roped%20in%20Alfred%20North%20Whitehead%2C%20the%20English%20mathematician%2C%20and%20philosopher%2C%20to%20inspire%20students%20and%20ignite%20their%20imagination.%20Donham%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20came%20to%20naught.%20Students%20and%20faculty%20evinced%20no%20interest%20in%20ethics%20and%20the%20social%20sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonham%20was%20a%20perspicacious%20educator.%20His%20premonitions%20were%20prophetic.%20Deprived%20of%20the%20emancipatory%20influence%20of%20the%20liberal%20arts%2C%20business%20schools%20uncritically%20disseminate%20discredited%20dogmas.%20As%20Jones%20argues%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20business%20is%20to%20generate%20profits%2C%20famously%20popularised%20by%20Milton%20Friedman%2C%20rests%20on%20a%20fallacious%20reading%20of%20Adam%20Smith%2C%20the%20putative%20founder%20of%20capitalism.%20He%20notes%20that%20even%20Adam%20Smith%20emphasised%20morals%20and%20believed%20that%20%E2%80%98markets%20would%20only%20deliver%20socially%20productive%20outcomes%20if%20ethical%20concerns%20guided%20businessmen.%E2%80%99%20Unmindful%2C%20business%20graduates%20work%20diligently%20to%20augment%20the%20investments%20of%20shareholders.%20Reversing%20this%20trend%20begins%20with%20recognising%20that%20deep%20responsibility%20is%20not%20an%20adventitious%20phenomenon.%20It%20is%20learned%20behaviour%20and%20must%20be%20consciously%20inculcated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20uplifting%20as%20deep%20responsibility%20is%2C%20it%20is%20not%20for%20everyone.%20Many%20try%2C%20but%20only%20some%20succeed.%20Jones%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20replete%20with%20business%20leaders%20who%20lost%20their%20way%20because%20they%20were%20over-optimistic%20or%20made%20myopic%20business%20decisions.%20Yet%20others%20succumbed%20to%20the%20siren%20song%20of%20Mammon%20as%20they%20tried%20to%20scale%20their%20business%20while%20professing%20commitment%20to%20values.%20Imbued%20with%20the%20sensibilities%20of%20a%20seasoned%20historian%2C%20Jones%20provides%20a%20rich%2C%20layered%20account%20of%20the%20agonising%20challenges%20of%20practicing%20deep%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaunting%20obstacles%20notwithstanding%2C%20entrepreneurs%20worldwide%20are%20drawn%20to%20the%20magnetic%20power%20of%20deep%20responsibility.%20They%20have%20forged%20a%20plethora%20of%20new%20initiatives%20%E2%80%93%20conscious%20capitalism%2C%20ethical%20investing%2C%20environmental%2C%20social%2C%20and%20governance%20(ESG)%20investing%2C%20and%20B%20corporations%20%E2%80%93%20all%20aimed%20at%20curbing%20the%20untrammelled%20forces%20of%20profiteering.%20B%20corporations%20are%20audited%20based%20on%20their%20finances%20and%20contribution%20to%20society%20and%20the%20natural%20environment.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20promote%20sustainability%2C%20human%20dignity%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98economy%20of%20communion%E2%80%99%3A%20using%20business%20to%20increase%20equality.%20There%20are%20currently%206000%20Certified%20B%20Corporations%20in%20over%2080%20countries%20and%20over%20150%20industries.%20Cassandras%20of%20doom%20might%20dismiss%20such%20efforts%20as%20%E2%80%98corporate%20greenwashing.%E2%80%99%20Yet%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Organization%20of%20Economic%20Cooperation%20and%20Development%20Report%2C%202020%2C%20the%20total%20assets%20under%20management%20that%20incorporated%20some%20element%20of%20ESG%20review%20and%20decision-making%20had%20reached%2011%20trillion%20dollars%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%2017%20trillion%20dollars%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20impressive%20accomplishment%20is%20the%20impetus%20for%20Jones%E2%80%99%20advocacy%20of%20deep%20responsibility.%20He%20knows%20it%20cannot%20save%20the%20world%2C%20but%20it%20can%20certainly%20help.%20Jones%20exhorts%20governments%20to%20modify%20policies%20and%20the%20legal%20context%20to%20incentivise%20deep%20responsibility.%20Business%20leaders%20also%20have%20a%20critical%20role%20to%20play.%20Jones%20urges%20them%20to%20refrain%20from%20distorting%20policy-making%20through%20lobbying.%20Business%20leaders%20must%20also%20avoid%20deliberately%20causing%20ecological%20and%20social%20damage%20to%20the%20people%20and%20the%20planet.%20They%20must%20be%20catalysts%20for%20innovative%20solutions%20and%20strive%20to%20create%20an%20ecosystem%20suffused%20with%20deep%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBadrinath%20Rao%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Sociology%20and%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20Kettering%20University%20in%20Flint%2C%20Michigan%2C%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20An%20attorney%20in%20the%20US%2C%20he%20is%20also%20the%20host%20and%20Executive%20Producer%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EIdeas%20and%20Insights%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20public%20affairs%20TV%20show.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692783031000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F23115646%2Fcharles-forerunner-3fPXt37X6UQ-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fcreating-a-deeply-responsible-path-to-doing-business%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20'Deeply%20Responsible%20Business%3A%20A%20Global%20History%20of%20Values-Driven%20Leadership'%2C%20Geoffrey%20Jones%20makes%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20reimagining%20capitalism%20and%20posits%20that%20the%20first%20step%20in%20this%20process%20is%20to%20reconceptualise%20business%20and%20its%20social%20purpose.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fcreating-a-deeply-responsible-path-to-doing-business%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Spicejet%20moves%20Delhi%20HC%20challenging%20order%20in%20favour%20of%20Kalanithi%20Maran%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692782653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-06%2F19%2Ffull%2F1655638490-7573.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fspicejet-moves-delhi-hc-challenging-order-in-favour-of-kalanithi-maran-123082300376_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20appeals%20came%20up%20before%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Yashwant%20Varma%20and%20Dharmesh%20Sharma%20which%20initially%20liste